    narr:narration """This hub gathers per-document **cadence** assessments under one rubric dimension — how rhythm, sentence-length variation, and structure shape readability. The dominant reading is remarkably consistent: nearly every child praises [varied sentence length](narr:Assess_Cadence_cm), [short punchy clauses with parallel structure](narr:Assessment_Cadence_1), triadic/rule-of-three patterns, and anaphora. Structural devices recur as cadence carriers: [bullets and sequence diagrams breaking dense prose](narr:Assess_Cadence_collective_memory), [section headers driving rhythm variance](narr:Assessment_Cadence_1), and [antithesis for impact ('weeks → days')](narr:RubricAssess_Cadence_GTM). The [voice-memo synthesis assessment](narr:RubricAssess_Cadence_20260107) names a 'before → after' drumbeat balancing long quotes against crisp metrics. The richest entry, [the multi-source rubric assessment](narr:RubricAssess_Cadence), holds several distinct verdicts at once — from 'exemplary staccato' to mixed transcribed speech. No dates attach to most children; this reads as a standing rubric library rather than a dated trajectory.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#Assess_Cadence_cm> ;
